Your 1 Rep Max (1RM) is the most weight you can lift once for an exercise. Many strength training plans require you to target a percentage of your 1RM. It can also be used to estimate the maximum you can lift for any repetition range.
• Estimate your 1RM for any of your exercises
• You can use your true 1RM
• View a 1RM percentage table
• See the estimated maximum weight for any repetition amount
• Update your 1RM at any time
